      • PhD

        public PhD(java.lang.String n,
           char g,
           int y,
           int m)
        Constructor 1: an instance for a person with name n, gender g, PhD year y, and PhD month m. Its advisors are unknown, and it has no advisees. Precondition: n has at least 1 character, m is in 1..12, and g is 'M' for male or 'F' for female.

      • PhD

           int y,
           int m,
           PhD adv)
        Constructor: a PhD with name n, gender g, PhD year y, PhD month m, first advisor adv, and no second advisor. Precondition: n has at least 1 char, g is 'F' for female or 'M' for male, m is in 1..12, and adv is not null.

      • PhD

        public PhD(java.lang.String n,

           PhD adv1,
           PhD adv2)
        Constructor: a PhD with name n, gender g, PhD year y, PhD month m, first advisor adv1, and second advisor adv2. Precondition: n has at least 1 char, g is 'F' for female or 'M' for male, m is in 1..12, adv1 and adv2 are not null, and adv1 and adv2 are different.

      • isYoungerThan

        public boolean isYoungerThan(PhD p)
        Group D.Group D: Write two comparison methods — to see which of two people got their PhD first and to see whether two people are “intellectual siblings” (i.e. they are not the same object and they have a non-null advisor in common). Write these using only boolean expressions (with !, &&, and || and relations <, <=, ==, etc.). Do not use if-statements, switches, addition, multiplication, etc. Each is best written as a single return statement.
